Detectives are continuing enquiries following a robbery in Paisley on Friday, October 24. Armed robbery in Paisley Detectives are continuing enquiries following a robbery in Paisley on Friday, October 24.Around 9.40pm hours a man entered the premises of Mamies Day to Day store in McKenzie Street and threatened staff with a weapon demanding money from the staff.No-one was injured in the incident; however staff have been left badly shaken by the incident.The suspect ran off in the direction of Tannahill Road, Paisley with a two-figure sum of money.There is a limited description of the suspect who is male and was wearing dark clothing.Detective Inspector Thomas Parker said: &quot;Officers are in the process of reviewing CCTV footage in an effort to gain more information about the suspect and the incident.&quot;It's imperative we trace the man responsible and I am appealing to anyone who may have been in area of Tannahill Road and McKenzie Street around the time of the incident to get in touch with us - you may think what you saw or noticed is unimportant but please do pass it on to police.&quot;Anyone with information is asked to contact officers at Paisley Police Office on the non-emergency number 101.Alternatively, please call Crimestoppers on 0800 555 111 where information can be given anonymously. 